---
import Cite from './Cite.astro';
import Button from './Button.astro';

const steps = [
  ['Describe', 'Ask for an outcome in ordinary language: data, explanation, triggers, actions and where the interface should appear.'],
  ['Inspect', 'Agent OS produces an explicit plan, provider list, data flow and capability diff before anything is installed or executed.'],
  ['Edit', 'Switch freely between natural language, Shortcut-style blocks and declarative source without changing semantics.'],
  ['Reuse', 'One micro-app instance renders as an AI response card, document block, notification, widget, watch glance or focused mode.'],
];

const examples = [
  ['UV today', 'Personal risk, safe-until time, hourly chart and sunscreen actions.'],
  ['Project overnight', 'Tasks, commits, messages and blocked decisions in one interactive brief.'],
  ['Travel disruption', 'Evidence, alternative routes, refund and share actions.'],
  ['Agent Mesh inbox', 'Pending, relayed, delivered and expired off-grid bundles.'],
];
---

<section id="micro-apps" class="section border-b border-border scroll-mt-24">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6">
    <div class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[.85fr_1.15fr] lg:items-start">
      <div>
        <div class="eyebrow mb-3">Micro-apps · Text-to-interface</div>
        <h2 class="text-balance text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight md:text-4xl">
          The interface you need should not require another app.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-pretty text-base leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground md:text-lg">
          Describe a missing interface, inspect the proposed data and authority, then install a small declarative micro-app. It can appear inside an AI answer, document, notification, lock screen, wearable, dashboard or full-screen mode. <Cite id="AOS-PROD-018" />
        </p>
        <div class="mt-7">
          <Button href="/micro-apps" variant="outline">Explore the builder</Button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-px overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-border bg-border sm:grid-cols-2">
        {steps.map(([title, body], i) => (
          <article class="bg-card p-6">
            <div class="font-mono text-xs text-signal">{String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0')}</div>
            <h3 class="mt-5 text-base font-semibold tracking-tight">{title}</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">{body}</p>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
      {examples.map(([title, body]) => (
        <article class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card/60 p-5">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold">{title}</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-xs leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">{body}</p>
        </article>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 rounded-xl border border-border bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-500/5 via-violet-500/10 to-teal-500/5 p-6 sm:p-7">
      <p class="max-w-3xl text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
        Micro-apps are safe to generate because the runtime accepts signed manifests over trusted components and typed actions — not arbitrary code with ambient filesystem, network or identity access. <Cite id="AOS-ARCH-026" />
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
